result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin E. Paulson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Restitution in the amount of $32.32 paid directly to the Clerk of Court's Office prior to sentencing.  The 10% surcharge in the amount of $3.23 still due and owing - same repayment conditions apply as noted below for the Costs.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  DNA sample to be provided to the Waushara Co Sheriff's Department no later than the close of business on April 8, 2016.

records.addlTxt: Restitution to Royal Supermarket - Ck No 011144

Case Called @ 11:00 AM: Defendant Dustin E. Paulson in court, appearing via telephone though the Court did not receive a request for him to appear via telephone.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  ADA states that something was said in the offer letter regarding his phone appearance.  Court notes that $32.32 Rest has been PIF previously.  Court entertains waiver of person appearance.  Court will permit telephone appearance at Def's request.  ADA argue for Court Costs as a sentence based upon full payment of Restitution.  Def confirms resolution.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea (IOWC):  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Statement by Def: None offered.   The Court:  Accepts resolution.  Imposes $32.32 Rest recognizing PIF and Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP. Costs to include DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  DNA sample to be provided to WCSD no later than 4/8/2016.    Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.

NOT PUT OF RECORD: Defendant Dustin E. Paulson in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Prior to going of record Court was made aware that Def did not qualify for SPD services due to earnings.  Def states he is disabled and would rather have counsel.  Def understands that he would be responsible for his Court Appt Atty's fees.  DA suggests one add'l STC as he will provide a written offer to Def.  P/S Scheduled - NOH Given.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 5, 2016 at 11:00 am.
Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment or maintaining any open checking accounts.

ADDRESS INFO for Dustin E. Paulson
Current: 3422 Boss Rd, Abbotsford, WI 54405   (Effective: 01-13-2016)
Prior: 208 S. 6th Street, Abbotsford, WI 54405
Defendant and Atty Szilagyi appear via video from the WC Jail.

RETURN ON WARRANT: Case called @ 1:14 p.m. Defendant Dustin E. Paulson in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. ADA Anderson requesting $1000 Sig Bond or low cash bond. Atty Szilagyi requesting signature bond. Court orders $1000 Sig Bond.  NGP entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for February 23, 2016 at 09:35 am.

Case Called @ 2:20 PM: Defendant Dustin E. Paulson not in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  In light of nonappearance, Arrest Warrant authorized with Statewide Extradition.
